{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}involve the community in a positive way \par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}can be implemented immediately \par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}are low cost compared to supply augmentation \par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}can save customers money on water usage. \par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}The main negatives associated with water restrictions were that they were seen to: \par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}rely on the action of the community \par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}be difficult to monitor and enforce \par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}be complicated to describe. \par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}[\'85] Participants noted that public communications campaigns are important to increase awareness of restrictions and the need for compliance. \par

\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-607\li607\sl240\slmult1\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\tx7280\tx7840\tx8400\tx8960\tx9520 pp. 20 WATER EFFICIENCY AND LOSS MINIMISATION (pp. 20)\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Love Water. In the recent drought this included a focus on business water efficiency programs aimed at identifying and repairing leaks as well as expanded education programs to encourage smart water choices such as shorter showers. \par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Economic Level of Water Conservation (ELWC) methodology will improve the evaluation of water efficiency initiatives and will guide utilities in their investments. \par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Water conservation played a key part of Hunter Water\rquote s response to the recent drought and included a range of community initiatives as well as a program of works to reduce losses from the network. \par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}HUNTER WATER ONGOING INITIATIVES:\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}SEE: Non-residential water efficiency programs  Water efficiency management plans and large non-residential customer engagement (pp.21, 11 industries/saving 360 ML in 2019-20. \par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Find & Fix initiative. Hunter Water deployed a fleet of 45 temporary data loggers during the year to help identify leaks at its sites and on customer assets including hospitals, schools, council and commercial sites /Water savings of around 670 ML /was the most effective water conservation initiative rolled out during the drought period/ The cost of this activity was $315,000 (Pp.21-22)\par

